I"é<p>Just like <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/breathwork-modulates-autonomic-arousal">breathing</a> and <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/optic-flow-modulates-autonomic-arousal">optic flow</a> can be <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/extrinsic-reward-dependence-is-unsustainable">exapted</a> as <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/agitation-can-be-weaponized">psychosomatic tools</a>, so too can <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/feynman-cluster-infuses-learning-by-teaching-with-social-structure">peer pressure</a>. Although arguably operating on a <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/triune-brain-model-classifies-brain-regions-through-evolutionary-lens">limbic, rather than autonomic, level</a>, <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/computer-networking-idealizes-social-structures">social structures might be engineered</a> <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/agitation-can-be-weaponized">to yield impressive results</a>.</p>
